University of Illinois at Chicago < University of Illinois at Chicago      Skip to Content  AZ Index  Catalog Home  Institution Home         Academic Catalog     Search Catalog               Undergraduate Catalog  Graduate Catalog  Print / Download Options  UIC Home         The University of Illinois at Chicago         Catalog Navigation  Catalog Navigation      Undergraduate Catalog  Graduate Catalog  All Course Descriptions          University of Illinois at Chicago       The catalogs are useful guides to UIC undergraduate and graduate programs, requirements, and policies. The catalogs include course information, program descriptions, degree requirements, campus resources and student services, and information about university and college policies and procedures.  Every effort has been made to make the undergraduate and graduate catalogs accurate at publication. However, all programs, requirements, courses, policies, and fees are subject to change by appropriate action of the faculty, the university administration, the Board of Trustees, and/or the Illinois Board of Higher Education.  The catalog is published by the Office of the Registrar (MC 003), 1200 West Harrison Street, Chicago, IL 60607; catalogeditor@uic.edu .          University of Illinois at Chicago   Apply Online | Contact Admissions | Privacy Statement Having problems accessing this site? Contact the Webmaster . Â© 2018-2019 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois    Back to Top   Print Options     Send Page to Printer    Print this page.    Download PDF of this page The PDF will include all information unique to this page.    Download PDF of the entire Undergraduate Catalog    All pages in the campus catalog.       Cancel    